title: Your Place For Fun
subtitle: Website for poker game with PayPal integration
stext: Play in Awesome Games Online
text:
Gaming Web & Mobile Development using already developed desktop game

I have a functioning desktop game of a new "patented" version of Texas Hold'em that needs a new gaming website to play it on with the ability to buy credits and add other games in the future. Not a white label site unless it's 100% owned. (client prefers wordpress/bluehost hosting)

Also, an app for the game itself needs to be developed. Timeframe is short. Target date by thanksgiving with minimal time margin.

If you can handle this type of coding and work. Looking for functionality most of all. If all goes well there will be ongoing work in the future.

I have a zip file for the game (desktop version) that needs to be put on a web platform and transitioned to mobile as well as mobile app.

Currently,I need to do a few things as this is a milestone project...

Website & Mobile Concept
  UI Design Completed & Tested Across All Browsers
  Client Approval Of Design Interface For Mobile
  Team Completes Functionality of Initial Gaming Website
  Test Social Media
  Provide Beta User Testing From Controlled Environment
  Debug with Information From Beta Users
  Usability Testing
  Cross Platform Testing
  Quality Assurance Testing
  Transfer Elements To Mobile Team For Development

Final Approval of Website For Launch
  Additional Quality Assurance Testing & Necessary Modifications Unassigned
  App Development Screenshots Submitted To Client For Final Approval

Mobile APK is Available For Download & Testing On Mobile and iPad Devices
  Beta Version of Site is "Live" for Client Approval and Internal Testing
  Quality Assurance Begins
  Usability Testing

Final Graphics & Sound added
  Beta Version Goes "Live" For Client Approval Prior to Submission To Google Play & Apple Store Unassigned
  Mobile Optimization For App Store
  Submission To App Store
  Submit App

I need to basically build the website and platform to play the client's game and obviously, create a system of buying credits to play...Cash for game credits etc.

Then we need to make it mobile friendly. Then build an app to allow people to play.
Also, the game graphics may need some upgrades, along with game sound effects.

If all goes well this will be the first of many projects and your pay will increase on future projects.
testimonials: Great skill and patience with a fluid and ever changing project. Overall a solid worker with very professional composure and character who delivers results.
image: 2018-12-17 You Place For Fun - home footer .png,2018-12-17 You Place For Fun - home games.jpg,2018-12-17-You Place For Fun - home head.jpg

title: OFN (Open Food Network) with some customizations for Africa
subtitle: Spree ROR and OFN customization and maintenance
stext: UI Design customization, deployment, mail setup and handling queue of messages, etc
text: We require a Ruby on Rails developer to further customise a customised spree instance optimised as a food network platform. The customisation is regional adaptation so currency, Country and state variables need to be updated. There is also a small amount of branding, ie adding of two logo's. A long term spinoff of this job would be to integrate components of the Spree setup with an existing Python Django web application and the ongoing maintenance of the code and application so we are looking for applicants who have Python Django skills as well as ROR skills.
testimonials: Dmitry was able to deliver on the requested work and beyond. Deadlines were met and his communication responses were prompt and very clear. He was also able to deliver on time and on spec. He continues to provide his services for general maintenance and updating of the site. We definitely look forward to working more with Dmitry in the future.

title: Wiki Timelines
subtitle: user collaborated project to build timelines on a wide ranging variety of topics
stext: Backend development and testing. Deployment on Linode Server.
text:
I have an idea I would like developing from scratch.

Forever updating topic pages which have stories added to them.

I create a topic page e.g. Barack Obama.

I then add stories regarding Barack Obama and each story gets displayed on the Barack Obama topic page. Stories get displayed in chronological order with latest story first.

Story 1: Barack Obama creates Iran deal
Story 2: Barack Obama re-elected.
Story 3: Barack Obama elected.
Story 4: Barack Obama runs for president
Story 5: Barack Obama born.

All these stories appear on the topic page Barack Obama.

Stories can be added/edited by anyone on the site (Wiki style)
testimonials:
Very happy with Dmitry. Went over and beyond to complete project even though half way through project it changed Scope.

highly recommend and thanks to him.

title: RME Shop with Custom Storefront Design
subtitle: based on spree-commerce with AJAX UI
text:
Looking to build a custom storefront for spree in Heroku. I have the mockup for reference.

Requirements---

1)This side bar must act like a filter for displaying products in the product viewer section (#2).

List all “material” types under the “Shop by Material” header
List all “category” types under the “Shop by Category” header
List all “brand” types under the “Shop by Brand” header
List all “Price” types under the “shop by Price” header
List all “Color” types under the “Shop by color” header
When a filter is applied, display only the products where the selected filter is associated with the product
Default display all products

2)This is the product viewer, where all products will be displayed based on defaults and applied filters.
- When a filter is applied display only the associated products
- The size of this viewer should be fixed at the top, but be inline at the bottom with the left side bar.
- Overflow of products should present a scroll option

3)Selected Product Display
Display <Image 2> for the “Selected Product” in the viewer.

4)Selected Product Details
-Display a header with the product concatenation “<Brand> - <Product Code>-<Price>"
-Display the products description in this box

5)Selected Product Viewer
-Display the most recently “Selected Product”
-When a more recent product has been selected, change the product to “Liked” and display in the “Items I like” viewer

6)Add to Cart
-When a product is in the “Selected Product” status, enable the “Add to Cart” button
-When the “Add to Cart” button is pressed, a confirmation pop up should be displayed
-When the “Add to Cart” button is pressed navigate to the “results page” and persist the product selection

7)Items I Like Section
-When a product from the product viewer has boolean “Liked” display it in this section
-Product overflow in this section should result in a scroll bar
-When a user clicks “Select” remove this item from the viewer and place it in the “Selected Product” viewer

8)Forgot 8...

9)Hovering over a product should display an enlarged preview modo, which displays <image 2>  associated with the product, and the “select” and “Like” buttons
- Each product should display the associated “Price” icon, and “Product Code”, under the image

10)Select Button
Adds the product into the product viewer
Displays <image 2> in the “Selected Product Display”

11)Like Button
- Adds the product to the “Items I Like” list viewer

12)Search Product Code
-When a user search by product code, display only the identified product in filtered results product viewer
-If no product is identified, prompt the user with a message that informs them “Unfortunately, we couldn’t find a match in our system. Be sure to include all characters includin

title: Social Services at Home
stext: Social services at home is one of the main forms of social services aimed at the maximum extension of stay of elderly and disabled people in a familiar social environment in order to maintain their social status, as well as to protect their legitimate rights and interests. Accomplished by providing citizens in need of permanent or temporary transient social services, partially lost the ability to self-service home care as a social and domestic, social and health services and other assistance.

title: Emergency Social Services: Social Worker
stext: Emergency Social Services is to provide emergency one-time citizens of the elderly and disabled people in dire need of social support. It may include the following social services: 1) a one-time provision in desperate need free hot meals and food packages; 2) provision of clothing, shoes and other essentials; 3) one-off material assistance; 4) assistance in obtaining temporary accommodation; 5) The organization of legal aid in order to protect the rights of people served; 6) the organization of emergency medical and psychological care, involving for this work of psychologists and the clergy and the allocation for the purpose of additional phone numbers; 7) other urgent social services.
